ARCUATE FASCICULUS

arcuate_fasciculus is the white-matter citizen carrying signals from wernicke_link to motor_speech inside fadriel_broca
in fadriel at two years old, the arcuate fasciculus is still myelinating: the fibers are forming their insulation but not yet at adult thickness
this is why fadriel can understand words his father uses but cannot easily produce them: the comprehension circuit is online, the production circuit is online, but the bridge between them is still being built

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fadriel_broca.zc
observe wernicke_link.rana
observe motor_speech.rana

the 7 properties of arcuate_fasciculus:
1 ENERGY zero point seven: moderate, fibers conduct but not at full speed
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE zero point three: positive
5 COHERENCE seven tenths: this is the developmental signature; an adult would be at nine tenths or higher
6 COUPLING zero point six: meaningful but not yet maximal
7 OBSERVER zero point two

VERB conduct
carry the signal from wernicke_link to motor_speech across the bundle of fibers
the speed of conduction depends on myelination state
right now, signals arrive at motor_speech with detectable delay relative to an adult brain

VERB grow
each successful conduction reinforces the fibers
the substrate's developmental program adds myelin where signals have flowed
this is how fadriel's vocabulary expands over months and years: not by learning words abstractly, but by his arcuate growing thicker each time he tries to say one

a fiber bundle is not just a cable
a fiber bundle is a citizen that learns by being used
the more fadriel speaks, the more arcuate myelinates; the more arcuate myelinates, the more fadriel can speak
this is the developmental loop that turns a two-year-old's halting words into a child's flowing speech
